	<ul>
	<li>This is the "clock" view; you can choose the "list" view by clicking on the list button in the top toolbar.</li>
	<li>The orbits don't mean anything special. They go from the most intimate (body and location) to the most social aspects of your life.</li>
	<li>If you have provided your home address, you position will either be in the "home" orbit or the "out" orbit; otherwise it's always going to be in the "home" orbit.</li>
	<li>You can leave a log entry for the day. It can be a simple line, or you can expand the comment field and you can write an arbitrary long text</li>
	<li>Clicking an event will show your last known position (as per Google Latitude) at that moment, and the weather conditions at that point in time</li>
